President Obama applauds Senators John Kerry and Joe Lieberman for their work in drafting the American Power Act, which aims to put America on a path to a clean energy economy. The legislation aims to create jobs in the renewable energy sector, reduce dependence on foreign oil, and protect the environment for future generations. The President emphasizes the need to reform the nation's energy policies and take control of the country's energy future. He calls for bipartisan engagement and hopes to pass the bill this year.